description:
## What

Implement the graph query layer in Go — CRUD operations for all node types, edge management, FTS5 search, and graph traversal using recursive CTEs.

## Context

Pure Go, uses database/sql with modernc.org/sqlite. All methods use prepared statements. Bulk operations use transactions. Same logical design as original plan, now in Go.

## Implementation

### GraphRepository (internal/graph/repository.go)
\`\`\`go
type GraphRepository struct {
    db *sql.DB
}

func NewGraphRepository(db *sql.DB) *GraphRepository

// Node operations
func (r *GraphRepository) InsertNode(node *db.GraphNode) error
func (r *GraphRepository) UpsertNode(node *db.GraphNode) error
func (r *GraphRepository) GetNode(id string) (*db.GraphNode, error)
func (r *GraphRepository) GetNodesByKind(kind db.NodeKind, limit, offset int) ([]db.GraphNode, error)
func (r *GraphRepository) DeleteNode(id string) error

// Edge operations
func (r *GraphRepository) InsertEdge(edge *db.GraphEdge) error
func (r *GraphRepository) GetEdgesFrom(nodeID string, kind *db.EdgeKind) ([]db.GraphEdge, error)
func (r *GraphRepository) GetEdgesTo(nodeID string, kind *db.EdgeKind) ([]db.GraphEdge, error)

// Search
func (r *GraphRepository) Search(query string, kind *db.NodeKind, limit int) ([]SearchResult, error)

// Graph traversal (recursive CTE)
func (r *GraphRepository) GetConnected(nodeID string, maxDepth int) (*SubGraph, error)

// Bulk operations (transactional)
func (r *GraphRepository) BulkUpsertNodes(nodes []db.GraphNode) (int, error)
func (r *GraphRepository) SyncScanResults(output *scanner.ScanOutput) (*SyncReport, error)
\`\`\`

### SyncScanResults
The key method for scan ingestion. Takes scanner output, diffs against existing nodes, upserts/deletes in a transaction. Returns SyncReport with counts.

## Testing

- [ ] Full CRUD for all node types
- [ ] Edge UNIQUE constraint enforcement
- [ ] FTS5 search with BM25 ranking
- [ ] Recursive CTE graph traversal handles cycles
- [ ] SyncScanResults is idempotent
- [ ] Bulk operations are transactional
- [ ] Performance: 200 node bulk insert < 100ms

